---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Azerbaijan Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/azerbaijan/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Georgia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/georgia' },
  { title: 'Turkey for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/turkey' },
  { title: 'UAE for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uae' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'azerbaijanFit', header: 'Azerbaijan Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'AZN$850-1,215/mo', azerbaijanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'AZN$995-1,420/mo', azerbaijanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'AZN$765-1,090/mo', azerbaijanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'AZN$710-1,015/mo', azerbaijanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (AzSigorta)', entryAge: '60', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'AZN$150-350/mo', azerbaijanFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'AZN$765-1,215', annual: 'AZN$9,180-14,580' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'AZN$1,050-1,620', annual: 'AZN$12,600-19,440' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'AZN$1,410-2,175', annual: 'AZN$16,920-26,100' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'AZN$50-150/visit', annual: 'Very affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'AZN$200-500/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Azerbaijan 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Azerbaijan. Baku's modern infrastructure, affordable living, Caspian Sea views, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Azerbaijan"
  subheadline="Azerbaijan offers oil-funded modernity, affordable living, stunning Caucasus landscapes, Caspian coastline, and warm hospitality—an emerging Eurasian crossroads for adventurous retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/azerbaijan-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Azerbaijan</h2>
  <p>
    Azerbaijan offers unique blend of East and West—oil-funded modern infrastructure in Baku, ancient Silk Road history, stunning Caucasus mountains, and Caspian Sea coastline. For adventurous retirees seeking affordable living with emerging-market excitement, Azerbaijan provides distinctive experience.
  </p>

  <p>
    Baku is the capital with best healthcare and modern amenities. The Flame Towers skyline and Old City UNESCO site offer contrast. Gabala and Sheki provide mountain retreats. Most expats choose Baku for healthcare access; explore regions for experiences.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Improving in Baku; limited elsewhere</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Azerbaijani; Russian common; English growing</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> AZN$1,500-3,000/month (~$880-1,760 USD); affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Subtropical (Baku); continental (interior)</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Oil wealth; Caucasus culture; secular Muslim</li>
      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Generally safe; avoid border areas</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Azerbaijan Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Azerbaijan healthcare is improving—Baku has modern private hospitals including Baku Medical Plaza, MedEra, and Central Clinic. Quality improving with oil investment. Outside Baku, healthcare is basic. Complex cases may need Turkey or Europe evacuation.
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare is limited. Private care in Baku is affordable and increasingly modern. International insurance with Turkey/Europe coverage recommended. Istanbul (2-hour flight) provides excellent backup for complex conditions.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Istanbul Backup</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Turkey provides excellent medical backup—Istanbul is 2 hours by air with world-class hospitals. Include Turkey in insurance coverage. Baku private hospitals handle routine care; Istanbul provides specialist backup for complex conditions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Azerbaijan has accessible visa policies:
  </p>

  <h3>ASAN Visa (E-Visa)</h3>
  <p>
    30-day electronic visa for most nationalities. Simple online application. Very straightforward.
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Up to 90 days. Extensions possible. Good for extended exploration.
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For stays over 90 days. Various categories including retirement. Apply through migration service.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residence</h3>
  <p>
    After qualifying period. Investment route available. Azerbaijan welcomes foreign investment.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Azerbaijan:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> May require travel insurance for visa</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Include Turkey/Europe coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Azerbaijan</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with Turkey evacuation coverage recommended. Baku private hospitals handle routine care well. Istanbul provides excellent backup for complex conditions. Regional coverage including Turkey, UAE, and Europe is ideal.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Azerbaijan, regional evacuation coverage important:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Azerbaijan</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong regional network, Istanbul access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Turkey access:</strong> Key regional medical hub</li>
    <li><strong>Improving locally:</strong> Baku care getting better</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with Turkey/Europe evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Azerbaijan (AZN ~1.7 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Baku base:</strong> Best private healthcare access</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Turkey network:</strong> Use designated hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> Caucasus/Middle East focused</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Oil Industry Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $4,000/month pension. Temp residence. Baku.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Middle East focus.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~AZN$900/month (~$530). Industry connection; regional backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Turkish Neighbor, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> TRY$50,000/month pension. Turkic connection. Baku.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with Turkey home coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~AZN$1,100/month (~$645). Cultural affinity; Istanbul backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Russian Speaker, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month income. Long-stay visa. Baku.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with CIS coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~AZN$820/month (~$480). Language ease; regional access.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Azerbaijan safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally safe—low crime in cities. Avoid Nagorno-Karabakh region and Armenian border areas. Baku is modern and secure. Normal urban precautions apply. Political situation requires monitoring but daily life is safe.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Azerbaijani?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Helpful but not essential—Russian widely spoken by older generation. English growing in Baku, especially in business. Healthcare providers often speak Russian. Learning basics appreciated but not required for daily life.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Azerbaijan Muslim?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes but very secular—Soviet legacy left Azerbaijan one of most secular Muslim-majority countries. Alcohol widely available. Western dress normal. Religious tolerance high. Modern, cosmopolitan atmosphere in Baku.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the visa situation?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Accessible—e-visa for 30 days very simple. Extensions and residence permits available. Not as straightforward as Georgia but workable. Investment options exist. Check current requirements as policies evolve.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Azerbaijan coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Azerbaijan authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
